# Soulless CHANGELOG - All Changes (as of 2026-04-10)

This file contains every "NEW CHANGE" comment from our editing sessions so you can audit side-by-side with the source files.
All original :: MRV comments are preserved untouched in the .rs files.

## Major Architecture Change (2026-04-10)
- Switched IN PROGRESS sections to stable ID format: `// - [ISSUE:module-001] Description`
- This enables the `board-sync.yml` workflow to automatically create GitHub issues and write back real `#123` numbers.
- All files updated to the new format.

## search.rs (17 edits total - different approach final version)
- Added `Utf32String` back to imports for on-the-fly scoring.
- `pattern.score(haystack.as_slice(), ...)` — final fix using the exact method the compiler suggested.
- Different approach: no more pre-stored `Utf32String` in `apps` vec. Temporary creation only during filtering (eliminates all method errors).
- Updated `load_desktop_entries()` helper to return simpler `(String, String)` tuple.
- Full explanation of why we don't use `widestring` or `std::path::PathBuf`.
- Added private helper `load_desktop_entries()` :: approval :: MRV
- Fixed all Utf32String method errors (as_slice, as_str, as_utf32str, etc.)
- Message enum derives Clone for iced 0.14 compatibility.

**New stable ID format added:**
- [ISSUE:search-001] Add fuzzy search ranking (trigram score + recency)
- [ISSUE:search-002] Improve keyboard navigation in results grid
- [ISSUE:search-003] Handle desktop entry placeholders (%u, %f, etc.) before launch
- [ISSUE:search-004] Make search helper zero-allocation where possible

